# Introduction to CSS

## What is CSS?

CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a stylesheet language used to control the appearance and layout of web pages.

CSS helps developers:

- Change colors
- Add spacing
- Control layouts
- Create animations
- Make websites responsive

Without CSS, websites would only display plain HTML content.

## Why CSS is Important

- Improves user experience
- Creates visually appealing websites
- Supports responsive design
- Separates content from presentation
- Reduces code duplication

## Real-World Example

HTML creates the structure of a login page.

CSS makes it attractive by adding:

- Background colors
- Rounded corners
- Shadows
- Responsive layouts

## Benefits of CSS

- Easy maintenance
- Faster page loading
- Consistent design
- Better accessibility

## Summary

CSS transforms simple HTML pages into professional and interactive websites.
